  + [source_002] is Caffarelli-Kohn-Nirenberg seminar notes on Navier-Stokes partial regularity
    = link: https://www.uni-ulm.de/fileadmin/website_uni_ulm/mawi.inst.020/skipper/NotesCKN_Jack_2.pdf
    = use: preserves accepted local regularity language for suitable weak solutions and local parabolic cylinders
  + [source_003] is Barker and Prange, From concentration to quantitative regularity
    = link: https://prange.perso.math.cnrs.fr/papers/survey-concentration-quantreg.pdf
    = use: frames concentration on small scales as a quantitative regularity problem rather than a direct global-norm decision
  + [source_004] is Quadrupole-Depletion Route to L3 Regularity for 3D Incompressible Navier-Stokes
    = link: https://quantumaetherdynamics.org/papers/Navier_Stokes_Millenium_Puzzle.pdf
    = use: source of the Theta functional and endpoint pressure-work target being tested

& [ResearchFindings] is the theorem-boundary result
  + [finding_001] is standard local theory supplies parabolic cylinders and scale-invariant quantities
